The paper deals with learning and estimation in relational models, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also discusses maximum likelihood estimation and statistical soundness, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of relational databases (cs.DB) and the characterization of relational polytopes (cs.SI).
